{
  "texts": [
    "Using the estimates in Figure 1 and assuming multiplicative improvement we would expect CEG gains of 3.43×.",
    "However, the efficiency gain is only 1.33×.",
    "In addition, we compare our default or \"Modern\" transformer (defined in Section 4.1.1) to our LSTM baseline.",
    "At a loss threshold of 5.3, we find a combined efficiency gain of 6.28×, whereas multiplying the individual improvements together, along with the LSTM to Retro Transformer improvements, yields a substantially higher predicted gain of 16. 66×.",
    "4 This suggests that multiplying individual improvements, estimated from ablation experiments, overestimates the impact of algorithmic improvements."
  ]
}